caption: Went on a Monday evening for a small birthday gathering, party of 4.  Parking right at the door.  We had a rooftop pod reserved and were seated immediately. I'm told by the person making the reservation that her ID and credit card info was held with the hostess for the entire visit.  Drinks and food served quickly.  Cocktail and drink list are extensive and food selections were varied but more limited, typical pub food. Staff was mindful, friendly and efficient. I feel we got what we paid for.  I'd visit again.

This is a great place with a  wonderful atmosphere. It has a nice view over the city of Chicago and great drinks and food to enjoy except for the rush vibes you get from the service. The thing that ruined our experience was when we went to the edge of the rooftop balcony to take some photos the busboys came to our table and cleared everything away, we were about 10feet apart from our table and we had drinks and food at our table and we also had two more drinks ordered from the waiter. So when we came back our table was completely empty. That’s why I would never come back here again
Awesome

This is a definite go to place if you're in downtown Chicago. Beautiful / Posh atmosphere overlooking the city with floor to ceiling windows with affordable and delicious food and drink menus. Tables are configured in groups and very COVID safe with how open the area is. Jarred is my go to there and is exceptional! All staff very friendly and great environment. A+++ ALL AROUND
Awful deposit and reservation rules.
Food was ok and a little too pricey but the atmosphere was amazing

My husband and I stayed at the Godfrey Hotel for Valentine’s Day weekend. We went to the rooftop bar for both the nights that we stayed and we had such a great experience. Covid precautions were well handled. The customer service was impeccable. The staff really made you feel welcome and almost as if we’ve known them from before. The cocktails were great and was made by the fantastic bartender named Trigger. We will definitely be back for a good time!

Oohhmygoodness. We had Rory as a server. He had great food and drink recommendations. We went for Valentine’s Day and he was amazing with taking  couple pictures and being so positive and making us so comfortable. Between our service and the food you couldn’t ask for more. Cannot wait to come back next time
Dope place ! I will be back better planned. Cool/hip chic lounge with good music and great food, the drinks here are lit.

So disappointed. We were so excited for our first igloo private dining experience in Chicago and it was absolutely horrible. What a waste of $1k!!!!  The zipper on the igloo was broken and it was freezing. They had to bring us another heater to keep us warm instead of moving us over to another one. It took our server 30 min to come and take our order after our full party arrived (mind you, we are on a time limit and we are stuck in an igloo, not that easy to go and get her). The food was cold and terrible. She didn’t write our order down so of course some of our orders were wrong and she forgot some of our drinks. She was clearly having a bad day and made it very clear she did not want to work there.  At the end of the night when we asked her to split the bill 3 ways, she got REALLY upset and walked out of the igloo and left the door unzipped purposely.  This was the worst service we’ve ever had. They didn’t even offer a slight discount for the inconvenience. What a joke!!!

Great customer service! Cold, but what can you expect lol it’s a rooftop lounge in Chicago so dress warm! We got the super premium package and it was well worth it! Try the shrimp sushi, sliders, and salmon avocado toast. All delicious!!!
What a great place!! Thought I'd be freezing but it was very comfortable 😌awesome night!!

Service was absolutely horrible. For the price paid for the big igloo for what should have been perfect for a birthday celebration was filled with frustration. The zipper on the igloo failed to work for the first 20-25 min of our time line with no adjustment for the inconvenience of freezing during this time while the mntce people worked on the zipper. Every simple thing we asked for like (a) chair for a person who had no seat (b) sauce for fries (c) straws- had to be asked repeatedly. We finally went and got a chair on our own so that the 6th person could actually sit down. All of our fries were too cold to eat when they finally brought the aioli which is why we even ordered them. The attitude of the hostess and our waitress was not nice and extremely pushy. The food was excellent which is why I added an extra star. I accidentally left my scarf and told my friend when I asked her to collect it for me since she stayed overnight there. They told her no scarf was left. I left from my hotel elsewhere to go back there to demand they bring me my scarf which I know is there. They literally brought it out in less than 3 minutes. Extremely poor experience and overpriced for such poor service. Go elsewhere.
This place is beautiful

Food and ambiance was great.  Server, Rachel, was great as well, however, 2 stars are based on my experience with management.  I went in today to get clarifications on the amount that I was charged for the Winterland Igloo deposit and was met with the Manager, Ashley, who provided poor, dismissive customer service.  On a beautiful Saturday afternoon a friend and I went to I/O during Brunch hours, we noticed the Mimosas kit on the brunch menu $50.  Our server, Rachel informed us that we could switch the deposit wine ($225) for mimosas and there would be a credit to the bill. Ok, sounds perfect.  Unfortunately, there was a misunderstanding, we would not be getting the Mimosa kit on the brunch menu but a higher priced champagne from the drink menu which was not explained at the time of ordering, a simple misunderstanding.  When going to speak with the Manager about the charge of the wine ($225) vs. the Mimosas  that were ordered, Ashley was kind enough to get a copy of my receipt but that's when the customer service ended. I attempted to explain what I was informed during our dining experience and tried to understand how the Mimosa kit turned into a $200 charge with no Mimosas on my receipt.  I was cut off multiple times, Ashley stated, "We don't need to explain it to you, it's written everywhere?" At this time, I'm trying to understand the charges, receipt and brunch menu, I ask Ashley, "Do you understand what I trying to say? " She replies, "No, I don't, because you're not making sense."  At what point in customer service do you tell a customer that they're not making sense when they're seeking to understand?  In short, my $225 wine deposit was switched for the $200 champagne. I do not mind paying for any experience or services rendered, the beignets, Benedicts, sliders, lamb chops and sweet potatoe skillet were great, however,  if I have questions or need clarity, I expect to be met with someone who's attempting to understand  my concerns and not be dismissive. There are so many tactful ways to handle customers and this definitely is not one of them.  Customer Service
(Translated by Google) Very poor igloos  (Original) Very earm igloos
Great staff and wonderful service. The igloos are a great away to sl celebrate on the rooftop. They are heated very well. No jackets inside required. It was almost too warm!
Incredible views & music. Pricey but worth it for a special event.
Really nice rooftop lounge/bar area.
Best in chicago
Food was amazing most definitely have to go back
It was just okay. Very pretty use of thr space considering dining restrictions.
Way over priced food was terrible
Nice. Clean. Expensive.  But some things worth price.

We went to the IO to celebrate two friends birthday’s and had a private igloo. I cannot describe how much fun we had. Not only were the drinks great, but our server was SO involved in making sure we had a great time. He was attentive and outgoing while making sure to be compliant with current COVID-19 guidelines and restrictions. Rory, if you’re reading this, THANK YOU FOR EVERYTHING!! The other staff members were also incredible and helpful. Cannot recommend this place enough. We had so much fun!!!

First of all. It’s not Rooftop. It’s just on 4th floor. Second of all they have wrong information updated on google. I went there yesterday. They closed at 10:30pm and they’ve written they are open till 1 am on Thursday night. Food was good. Cocktails were good. I just wish they had more alcohol in them Coz they were very bland.
Decent view menu needs improvement.
Amazing food, views, aesthetics and service
Great place, great service. Would recommend.

I am truly impressed with this resturant. I travel often and experience a wide range of food resturants and Hands done, this restaurant was one of the best efficient servers, we received our food QUICKLY and the quality of the food was amazing. The commitment in serving us was outstanding. I would definetly come back if I visit Chicago again.

Even with the restrictions to dining going on. Great food, great ambiance and amazing service. Very cozy and warm igloo experience made us feel relaxed and special. Even though it's normal for this establishment to have these out during this time of year, it felt even better knowing we were privately enjoying our meal amongst the pandemic. Food and drinks were prompt, and we were checked on very frequently by patient and enthusiastic waitresses and hosts. And the food was incredible, try the lamb lolichops and the salmon, cooked to perfection, and the steak tacos were amazing for appetizers. Being on a rooftop with spectacular views to experience our first dine "out" experience in chicago couldnt have been a better choice.  Would 5/5 come again.
Great food!  AMAZING ROOFTOP AESTHETIC!!!  Can't wait to go back!!!!

We had such a great time tonight in our heated igloo. Mike was an awesome server. We had a wonderful anniversary there, although they could have mentioned it when it was on our reservation.  Food was great and not to pricey for the city. drinks were awesome. Igloos were cozy warm. I would highly recommend. I told my wife it is a definite go to for my birthday in January, especially during Covid!
A bit on the pricier side. Such a great place to dress up and get great drinks. The food is delicious and
Very nice venue.  Large in/out mid-rize deck.

We had a really great experience. The food was good. The views were great. A little pricey for the food selection but the ambience makes it worth it. Service was okay and definitely worth another trip. Covid precautions were in place and respected.
Great vibe but their signature cocktails aren’t made with any ice and are overly foamy. I’d come back here during the summer when there’s no COVID!

Do not eat here!  Ate the grilled octopus last night and got food poisoning.  Started vomiting exactly 6 hours after eating there. Called today to talk to someone at the restaurant and there is no one that answers the phone and the voicemail is full. Called the hotel front desk and they were unhelpful and after I said I’m trying to avoid writing a bad review. She said she didn’t care and to go ahead and write the bad review. Save yourself a lot of pain and avoid this restaurant and hotel at all costs.
Worst place ever .....

Pretty decoration, but we order a Steak (medium) it was burn, we order a melon mojito that was $52, a jar , full with ice no mint and no taste at all About the view, this roof bar it’s at 4th flour and no view
Had my birthday celebration there. Beautiful, good food, nice staff. A little pricey, but I think it worth it.
Beautiful
Don’t wast your time or money

If I could leave zero stars I would. Jared was a horrible waiter, worst I ever had in a fine dining setting.  my card had over 2,000 dollars on my account and tried to come at me like my card “declined”. So embarrassing, used three different Chase cards and he tried to make it our fault because “we used Chase”. So disrespectful after we spent about $400 there. Had to run to the ATM and pay in all cash, he never once said sorry or tried to explain why THEIR card machines didn’t work. So rude the entire time we were there. Will never come back and tell all my friends never to come back.

Nice scenary. Went during covid precautions. Pretty decent drinks.had the burger which was great. Tacos were ok and not that filling tbh. Not a fan of their fries either. Always comes out tasting a little burnt. Overall service was great. You will get charged for the water in case that matters to you. Outside flooring on the patio opposite the bar  is a little shaky,  so if you're a "bad B" in stilettos, you've been warned you might bust your ish. Other than that a really good time with proper solid views of the city. Plan on going again for sure.

Upscale place. Very visually appealing the rooftop bar is beautiful although the process of making a reservation is convoluted and requires jumping through more hoops than necessary. In order to avoid the deposit required for reservations I would recommend setting a reservation through email they respond rather quickly

Dear management of IO Godfrey. Can you please explain to me how your customers can call your establishment for three days straight during normal business hours to discuss an issue with you and you can not even answer your phone. Either someone at your front desk is not doing their job or people are letting it ring deliberately. Seriously disappointed. Please pick up your calls so you can speak to your customers about their concerns. Thank you
Had an amazing time with great views. Socially distant tables and masks required. Wonderful way to celebrate my birthday

Was sat in direct sunlight and asked to move when the place was empty when we got there and left but said there were no open tables. That was the start then only talked to our server twice in an hour. No one said have a nice day or anything they were all on there phones. Very disappointed and won’t be back and wouldn’t recommend to anyone.

Took my friend from out of town here and everything was amazing. Good food, good drinks and the view was nice. The waiter was amazing and attentive, he did not disappoint. I highly recommend and I will be back

The customer service was awful. The server was really rude. We were celebrating my friends birthday so we wanted to get her a cake when we ordered a cake our server said oh the kitchen is closed but she never mentioned the last call to order anything and the kitchen is closing. I understand they close at 11 but we were paying our bill to leave but the security came with a bad attitude and wanted to kick us out. The security took off his mask and started yelling at us and standing too close to our face. It ruined our night. We almost paid 700 dollars for this restaurant. If you want to enjoy your night do not go to this restaurant.
Due to COVID I understand some of the lack but the music sucked and we were not able to sit at a table and the food was thrown together!

The worst services I have ever encountered. We made a reservation and when we got their they were gonna be out on a bar when there were so many open seats. They then moved us to a different place and when we asked to moved somewhere else they refused and I noticed that the place next to us that we wanted to be seated at wasn’t even occupied the whole afternoon. The waitress was a nightmare. We weren’t able to finish are order since she kept running away. We had to call her back around 3 times just to get our food order in. I didn’t want to make it a race thing but that’s what it was. Later on another family came in and they were african American  just like us. I noticed how different we were being treated. Non the less we tried to make the best of it but I would not recommend this place if you’re African American. I saw a recent review just like this but I overlooked it. Definitely won’t be going back there again. A place this beautiful shouldn’t have ignorant people.

I went there on Saturday the 1st of August with some friends to celebrate a birthday party. The view was nice the drinks were ok and the food was great. I work in the service industry and I am so upset at the service we had. Servers are supposed to check if everything is ok. It seemed like they did not care we were there. And no smile and looked like she did not want to be there. We only got asked 2x if we needed anything. We had to get our server Lauren’s attention to get drinks. In the section we were at was not busy at all. I’d understand if y’all were busy. The Server also works on her tips, which is why we did not leave any.  I don’t even think the service fee of $52.71 should not be included because the Service was not great.

Came here for brunch with a reservation. Beautiful location, but questionable customer service. First, when my party was seated for lunch, they only provided a cafe style end table to eat. The place was about at 30% capacity, but when requested to take another vacant reserved table, we were denied. We then were placed in an incredibly hot seat on the other side of the restaurant. When the waiter came out and asked  did the table have any allergies, I responded a dairy allergy to which the waiter scoffed. Already jaded by the experience thus far, the waiter let us know that they had no tap water only Fiji. Once we decided this location was not the choice, we left $10 on the table to cover the water because we couldn’t find our server. At this point, we were followed out to the server’s desk because the water was $11.48. Instead of inquiring about the experience, we were tracked for $1.50. As we were then asked did we won’t to make a reservation for later that evening when it cooled off. That was an easy answer — no! Won’t be back.

Beautiful place. They had two sides. We came all the way from a different state very excited to visit this spot. I was very disappointed with the service. I do understand that there is reservations but we could have been placed on one of the tables until the other parties are arrived. We were placed under the sun. Mentioned that we have dairy allergies and the waiter wasn’t very happy about it. We did leave money on the table and the host followed us to the door asking for a $1 when we were there for less than 5 minutes. Will not be back.
We ordered the baked chicken and lollipop lamb....and it was seasoned to perfection. Great customer service and beautiful view!
Service was just okay. Felt the waitress was a bit neglectful and cold. Food was just okay as well. Mimosas were good.
The service from Trigger was excellent.

This was my son's & I first outing since COVID. We were originally sat at a table in direct sun on the rooftop, but our server Dalton was amazing!  He was able to move us in a shaded area under an umbrella & we felt comfortable since their were no other patrons around us. 100% the best experience for us who were nervous about going out during COVID. I suggest requesting Dalton as your server for he is kind, friendly & very helpful...also gives great recommendations on the good eats. This is one of our favorite places & will be back. Thank you Dalton for making my son's 13th birthday brunch a very nice experience! Would give 10 stars!

Love this place on every day except Friday and in particular Saturday poser day. Nice people, great service, highly diverse clientele. Just a great place for drinks, food, to see and be seen (in a non-meat market way.) Great music. Real people, real interaction. Wide age range.

With COVID, we had to reserve a table vie Email.  I specifically stated it was for two people AND it was our 20 year wedding anniversary.  We get there to have them seat us at the BAR right next to the tubes for the beer pumps for God's sake.  Are you kidding me?  We asked to be seated at a nice L shaped sofa like several two person couples were or just a table not the bar and we were told that was our only option or we could sit in two chairs with a small end table between us.  We asked to speak with a manager, no one came out.  The same hostess who kept repeating that other tables were for parties with more people came back and then told us we could sit at a six person counter height table now.  They were not willing to give us a smaller more intimate table or sofa but I guess we could have a six person counter height table?  Another employee comes out and begins to argue with us and tell us that the bar is considered a table and that's just the way it is.  Needless to say we left.  No thanks.  Super rude and just wanted to stick us anywhere to fill up space.  Ashley the manager who booked the reservation never once mentioned yeah we're gonna stick you at the bar for your 20 year anniversary dinner.  Stay away!

My wife and I struggled for days to make a simple reservation. After countless emails and phone calls we finally were able to confirm a reservation for our anniversary.  When we arrived at the restaurant, the host said we were not on the reservation list. We then showed him the text message confirmation for the correct date and time and he kept telling us that it was only a confirmation to get on the wait list. (No where on the confirmation did it say wait list)  We were finally able to talk to the manager and she tried to tell us that our reservation was for the day before. We again showed her our confirmation and she finally admitted that she may have made a mistake. Apparently the host completely lied to us about the so called “wait list.”  After 20 minutes of all this, they finally said they would find room for us, as if it were our mistake. At that point we were too upset to accept and decided to find somewhere else to spend our money.  If this restaurant doesn’t care about a couple with a reservation on their anniversary, I can’t imagine they care about any other customers either.

‪@iogodfrey This is probably one of the worse experiences I’ve had on a rooftop party. It took nearly 40 mins to get a drink and we had call a manager to help speed up things. Drinks are mediocre at best. Basically, it’s not all that. Pick another rooftop venue. #disappointed ‬

The view was amazing. Everything was great until we were escorted out for no reason. We were the only Black party at the venue & when the night was over we were aggressively escorted out as white parties were able to finish their drinks. For a group of Black women it was intimidating to have a man handle us the way he did. We should have looked at more reviews because we are not the first to be treated in this way. The lounge is clearly whites only - rich whites only
Nice place but the waitresses kind of ignored us for a while and the lady host was very rude! Not sure why..
I celebrated my birthday every spring for past 3years here! Love it!

Great views. Tasty drinks and food. It's a great date place as well as a place to hang out with a group of friends.  Service is fast and friendly as well.  I really like this place and we've gone on multiple date nights in the past!
Beautiful rooftop venue with nice indoor and outdoor spaces to host events. Will be back soon!
We have been working with the Godfrey for over five years. One of our favorite event spaces in Chicago!
Loved this hotel rooftop, the Wagyu burger was delicousss ... the vibes were awesome! ♥️

Pricey, but great food and drinks. Absolutely beautiful inside. The waiters were very friendly and patient. Food took awhile to arrive, but the shrimp tacos were so good we ordered another round. Overall great for a chill and laid back experience.

Love the vibe!

Amazing happy hour from 4-6, definitely get the sliders, fries and the shishito peppers. Do not get the lettuce wraps! Service is amazing. This place has an amazing view of the city but it’s on the 3rd floor of the Godfrey so you have to go through the hotel but it’s awesome. Better view of the city than a view from downtown. Amazing Halloween party every year.
Excellent great atmosphere great view good service

My friend was new in town and we wanted a place to chill out while he waited for his departure time. We found this place and honestly its a very awesome place. Nice and Comfortable lounge. I was more impressed with the amount of time the waitress kept checking on us if we wanted anything. That’s absolutely top notch customer care. My meal wasn’t enjoyable tho. Nevertheless my friend enjoyed his.
Great atmosphere and right in downtown Chicago!

Husband took me here for our 2 year anniversary and absolutely loved everything about it. The food was amazing, the view was amazing and the service was great. The prices were not bad at all for what we got which was great. Server always checked up on us to make sure everything was okay. She also Gave us complimentary champagne to celebrate our two year anniversary. I would definitely recommend this place for any special events or even to hang out and have a nice relaxing time with friends. We will be coming back for sure! Thanks for a great experience!
N8ce atmosphere
Awesome views and cocktails to go with it!
Might not have the best views but.for the experience it's worth checking out
Exceptional views,  cocktails and food.

Our stay at this hotel so far has been very disappointing. We've booked 6 nights and 7 days at the Godfrey. On Saturday night we thought to give the I|O bar a try and the customer service was terrible. We took the elevator down to the 4th floor and were told that we had to go to the lobby for wrist bands even though we are staying on the premises. We venture down just to show our IDs then ushered to the elevator to come back to the 4th floor and when we walked back into the bar no one checked our bands. We proceeded to the bar and bought two drinks from a bartender that obviously can't speak more than 7 words, "You wanna open or close your tab". After standing we notice tons of tables so we asked one of the bar girls where can we sit to not interrupt reserved seating, she pointed to a section and before we could sit down the hostess both said we couldn't  sit there. We advised that the bar girl said we could and they told us we can sit anywhere else. We then walked to the opposite side of the bar and sat down in a booth in the back (mind you there were 7 or more tables available). One hostess rushed over to say we couldn't sit there. We then asked where we CAN sit to enjoy our beverage and she said no where. She didn't ask if we wanted the bottle service.., she just assumed we couldn't pay for it. Coming here after spending $400 at Chicago Cut was disheartening. We hold all corporations at a high standard. Our next visit to the Windy City we'll be choosing a different hotel. If I could choose ZERO stars I would however the option was unavailable.

I was a part of a bar crawl recently and I|O was our second stop. I absolutely loved this bar, the vibe was chic, the sushi was amazing, and they're was a variety of delicious sweet drinks to choose from. We were outside on the patio and the views were outstanding. Everyone in our group was snapping pic after pic. I would go back in a heartbeat.
Fantastic event space (rooftop), excellent service,  easy in and out. Don't miss an event held here.

Was invited to come in and enjoy a few appetizers and drinks at the rooftop after a long work week. There were no large tables that we can all sit for 16 people but manage to sit in the couch area with additional stools.  The menu had some unique mixed drinks like the watermelon margarita and the dragonfruit mojito which was a delight to drink with the gorgeous roof-top view of the city. The service was impeccable and what we ordered for food and drinks came fast.  So why the bad marks, well I went to the washroom to freshen up and to my surprise I was stopped by the hostess and asked me where I was going? I mention I am sitting there as I pointed to the large booth and then he told me to take off my cap, which I was wearing that as I came here a few hours ago.  I asked if there is a dress code and he told me yes, it started at 8pm. Dress code posted is "wear smart and casual - elegant attire".  All I ask if there is a dress code, tell me before I enter not after spending hours there.  I guess I will think twice to recommend this place for drinks or come here before 8pm.
Top notch service
Nice and fun
The rooftop is nice, the drinks and service were great, but the food was absolutely terrible. Just the worst. Would recommend as a place for drinks only.
Nice place to relax
It's not even on the roof but whatever Drinks were cool overall

This wasn’t my first time coming here and I really enjoyed my previous  visits. However, I hosted on Saturday and sat a the bar with my friend. We asked to see a menu and when we ordered, a gin & tonic, the bartender proceeded to tell the other bartender in a laughing matter: “a whole lot better than a corona” Mind you we are people of color and that was just completely disrespectful.

very nice rooftop!

Awesome views, great views and fantastic food!! We visited it twice over holiday weekend and it wasn’t crazy busy either night. This place should be busier.
My only experience was on Saturday night which is like a nightclub. It was very crowded. DJ played house music. The bar/bartenders are pretty good
The food and drinks were so good! We had a super delicious Long Island. The atmosphere made us believe we were in Miami.

Nice and stylish place. Lovely atmosphere and well organized and well dressed waiters. They are very polite and they knew their job very well. This is a place that is worth to visit. Food and beverages deserve a high rating, especially the cocktails. I recommend this place, I really had a nice afternoon with my family and friends. Next time I am in Chicago i will definitely visit this place.
Not my favorite, wait staff unfriendly.

Guest of the hotel. Figured we would stop in for a night cap. Took 35 minutes before we were even waited on and never saw the waitress again until we tried to leave. Better dress like money or good luck getting any attention from staff.
The atmosphere is cool. Not much on the menu though.

Loved it. Great time. Lots of mingling. Good drinks.  Will definitely go again.

It was a great place. We had bottle service for my friends bday and had two reserved spots right up front with a great view of the city.

Terrible experience. I purchased three bottles on my 40th birthday here with table service. I had originally placed 5 to be on my table but needed to add 3 more. The doorman Lance made me pay him 50 dollars to get 3 more people upstairs to skirt the line. When one more friend showed up he demanded another 55 dollars and made me give him my license which he held until I came back with money. I spent well in excess of 1000 dollars on that table and it ruined my birthday that this type of extortion happened. I came to visit from NYC to this place with close friends. It's sad that it culminated with this experience. I hope the manager reads this and addresses this. I am happy to give details of my bottle reservation as well. Waitress was fantastic btw.
A beautiful rooftop! The view is not as great as many other locations but the food, drinks, service and music make up for it.

The drinks were horrible.  I ordered a margarita with salt on the rim. And got a sugary drink. The margarita was very sweet with sugar on the rim. My sister order a Moscow Mule and it tasted  like they pulled the ginger from the ground and threw it in the drink. In her words the drink taste like dirt. Will not be visiting again
Stopped in for a drink. Rooftop was mostly closed. Great place to lounge. Trendy and classy.
Nice place, watch out for the gold diggers.
Great place with great food and drinks!

I really liked this place a lot. I'm sure it's much busier in the summer months when you can actually go outside. It's located on the rooftop of the Godfrey Hotel. The bartenders were really cool but the drinks are a little bit on the pricey side. I'm from Miami so I'm used to it but if you're used to 8$and $9 drinks this is not the place. I didn't get a chance to try the food but I saw some plates come out that looked very delicious. The decor is very chic and so was the crowd. There was a doorman downstairs but he didn't give me any problems coming in. I was dressed in a suit which I thought was appropriate for the environment. For more interesting reviews and places to visit check out @ricklemoinevip
Very nice place.  Great drinks and small plates that you can share as a group.  Drinks are made worth the cost and for those of you that like CBD, they have the oil they can add to your drink.
10 bucks to take a pic by the fence. First and last time here
Amazing staff, very courteous, excellent attention to detail. Food was delicious.
Great rooftop for renting for your party
Nice place great virws
Awesome rooftop with an amazing view!!

Rooftop drinks at a great location in River North. Bottle service is spot on, wait and servers are top notch. Definitely will return for dinner and drinks on the patio. Valet parking for the hotel is $$$$.
Beautiful rooftop lounge with great views and tasty cocktails
Went with a group that reserved an area - very nice place, excellent waiting staff, great food and drinks
Great ambience, food was OK, music was too loud for me

If I could give this place zero stars, I would. I came here with a group of friends and family to celebrate my 21st birthday on 2/16/19, and I was completely embarrassed and disgusted with how we were treated at the door. Prior to arriving, I spoke with two people that worked there. During the first conversation, I was inquiring about table reservations, and I was given the price points of the bottle services. However, at no point in that was it stated that large groups HAD to reserve a table with bottle service. On another occasion I spoke to Ashley Kelly, the general manager. I asked her if there was any list we needed to get added to to ensure entrance, she said no. So you can understand my confusion when we arrive and BRAD, the door manager tells us we cannot enter without a table reservation. From the very beginning BRAD was rude and unwelcoming. He stated that because we were a large group we had to reserve a table to ensure we wouldn't congregate in one area, and when I asked where this policy came from, seeing as though it was never explained in either of my previous conversation with IO employees; he stated that it was on the website (my entire group checked the website, it is not stated on there) and it has always been their policy. So after continuous questioning about this phantom policy, BRAD slips and says that this rule is not only to ensure we don't congregate but to ensure that large groups spend a certain amount of money. So not only is there no room in a lounge for a large group, now we are also being turned around because he is assuming we won't spend any money. As if this isn't bad enough, as I'm speaking with BRAD, the door manager a group of 10 plus (that does not have a table reservation), enter. To everyone's surprise, they are allowed in. So when we see them entering, I ask BRAD why they are being allowed in since they also do not have a reservation. His reasoning was that they know one of the bartenders. So I asked how does he know that they won't congregate or spend a lot of money, being as though these were the reasons why we wouldn't be let in. He says that "there is an exception to every rule." So is the problem that we will congregate or is it that we won't spend enough money? Or is the problem that we don't know the right people? Or is it that we didn't fit the image of BRAD's ideal patron? Whatever his reasoning is, it is complete nonsense and made up in his tiny brain. I will never return to this DISGUSTING establishment.

A group of family/friends and I went here this pass Saturday (2/16/19) to celebrate a 21st bday. Before even coming to the lounge the bday girl was in contact with a manager to ensure there would not be any issues with our group coming to the lounge without any table reservations. Of course when we got there it was a different story. We were turned away by Brad (who introduced himself as the door manager). He told us we could not come in because we were a large group and we might not spend money without a table reservation It was extremely disheartening to be treated in such a horrible manner. For Brad (door manager) to assume we were not going to spend money is insulting and all of the lies he told was very frustrating. We were celebrating a birthday...why wouldn't we go and have a great time and spend money!!. I WILL NEVER go here again and I will definitely spread the word. Poor poor customer service. And to add insult to injury BRAD proceeded to allow a large group (who did not have table reservations...we asked them) to go up without any trouble. Please beware of how this business treats their customers. Do not go here. Especially if you are African American...they will treat you less than!!!

ZERO STARS, I excepted more from this establishment and they have disappointed me to the upmost. My family and friends were at Godfrey this past Saturday 2/16/19, for my Goddaughters 21st birthday. The moment we walked in the door, Brad the "Door Manager" said we were not able to enter the rooftop lounge because we were a big group. The birthday girl communitacted with a manger at Godfrey and was not told that if she was to have her group join them on Saturday without an reservations, we would be denied entry. I never been denied entry into an lounge or bar when being with 10 or more family and friends, but Brad made the decision not to let us in. He couldn't provide roof of the "policy", he said it's on the website and the site does not state big groups are not allowed without reservations, but then allowed a group of 10 people who happened to be caucasian without reservations right in front of us. I asked if they had servations and they said NO. Again Brad still decided not to let us in. I told my Goddaughter not to worry about it, when you are treated this way, you do not give an establishment your money, nor continue try to understand what the issue is, cause you will never get it. I found may other establishments area the area, who I knew would except us and we went to Sound Bar and had a GREAT TIME, my Godaughter, family and friends had an Amazing time at Sound Bar. She enjoyed her 21st Birthday and that's all we all wanted for her. GODFREY GETS NO STARS FROM ME AND TO HAVE SOMEONE LIKE BRAD REPRESENT YOUR ESTABLISHMENT, WHO DENYS SOMEONE TO ENJOY AN EVENING WHERE SHE WAS LOOKING FORWARD TO SPEND HER 21ST BIRTHDAY OR ANY CELEBRATION IS WRONG. WHEN DID IT GET TO A POINT WHERE YOU ARE NOT ALLOW TO ENJOY MUSIC, FOOD AND DRINKS IN THE CITY OF CHICAGO? THANKS TO BRAD, I WOULD NO LONGER COME TO GODFREY. This is discrimination and something needs to be done about this.

If I could give this place 0 stars, I would. Now this is the second time I've had problems with this place and it will be the last!!! Me and a group of friends and family came here to celebrate a 21st birthday. Before even coming, I emailed a woman named Kayla, who is a hostess at the IO Godfrey. I asked her if there was any kind of list we needed to be on because there was a group. She told me no, but people with table reservations would be seated first. That's understood!! Then, the manager Ashley emailed the birthday girl of our group and told her there is no list, we would be able to come, but it would be standing room only. Ok, that's understood again. As soon as we walk in, they have the door manager BRAD, who was extremely rude from the very beginning, who basically wouldn't let us in because we were a "large" group. He said it was policy and on the website, which was his first lie, because I have yet to find the policy and he couldn't even show us. Then, said the space isn't made for large groups to congregate. BUT if we wanted to pay for a table then we could go up and congregate. So you're telling me your establishment is not made for big groups, but if we buy a table you can accommodate a big group? Hmmmm how stupid does that sound? Now you're lying to me again, BRAD. Then, he said they can't just have us all standing around congregating. I'm sorry, what difference would it make if we all came in pairs of two or four once we were in the lounge, we still would have been socializing together because IT'S A LOUNGE AND PEOPLE SOCIALIZE!!! Then BRAD makes a statement about people not buying drinks. Now we're getting somewhere, BRAD!!! I completely understand it's about money, but for you to automatically assume that because we are a group and we didn't pay for a table, which we didn't want anyway, that we would go up and not buy drinks is extremely insulting. You know what they say about assuming! Like we seriously were here to celebrate a birthday. What would make you think we weren't going to buy drinks? So, next we asked for the manager Ashley, just to get clarification and BRAD said she was upstairs and didn't want to come down. Not understanding, if she's a manager why wouldn't she come down? That's bad business and customer service on her part. THEN TO MAKE MATTERS WORSE.... as we are standing trying to understand BRAD's logic, he literally let a whole GROUP of 10 people, who I will state were all Caucasian, in to go up right in front of us and guess what?!?! They didn't have table reservations, because we made sure to ask them as they all were filing in line.  But since they knew somebody there, they were allowed to go up. Hmmm now, there is a bigger problem. Oh and interesting enough someone in our party was actually texting Ashley about what was going on, and she stated that she wasn't even on the premises. Hmmmm so who is lying and what is the reason for lying? This is my second time having an issue with this establishment and the last. Not wanting to make this a racial issue, but it clearly is and in 2019, people will not tolerate the disrespect. Our group gladly took our money to Sound Bar Night Club and the birthday girl had an amazing 21st birthday. That was your final time, IO Godfrey, and I will make sure to make others aware of how you treat people who just want to come and have a good time like everyone else!

This is my third and FINAL time dealing with this establishment and their seemingly race driven policy implementation. Last night, I and a group of friends decided to enjoy a friend’s 21st birthday at this location. Prior to this night, my friend spoke with the manager regarding her party attending. At that time, she was told the price of bottle service. It was never explained that bottle service was required for a certain size party. So last night, the birthday girl and twelve others arrive, at the same time, to go celebrate. At this time, we were stopped and told that in order to get in, we needed to purchase a table and bottle service (something  that was never mentioned during that previous call). We were also told that it is on the website (never found it). The reason given? They don’t want such a large group congregating in one spot. Is it not a social event? Everyone is congregating, but I digress. Now, this would have simply been an issue of slime balls trying to get money UNTIL less than five minutes later, a just about equal, maybe even larger, sized group of Caucasian people (no disrespect to them), male and female, were allowed to go up without bottle service or a table. The justification? “They know a bartender up there.” So, us “congregating” would have been allowed if we knew one person who worked up there? Sure. Needless to say, individual parties in our group reached out to the manager same manager from the previous call. She refused to come down and speak with anyone. I don’t want to make this a racial issue, but again, this is my third time dealing with these phantom rules that came out of the sky upon my arrival. Another individual in the party and friends (group of four this time) were turned away because her name was not on a list. Mind you, when she called prior to the night, a list was never mentioned. I won’t get into the details of the third incident, but just to be clear, it was centered around the same imagination station policy. This is embarrassing and disgusting. I am extremely disappointed and refuse to allow them to humiliate me again. But before I ban them from my life, I will share my experience and make others aware of this establishment’s hypocrisy.
